wikipedia_page.main: Gary S. Stebbing (born 11 August 1965) is a former professional footballer who played in The Football League for Crystal Palace, Southend United and Maidstone United. He was signed from the Crystal Palace junior ranks in 1983 and went on to play 102 times in the Football League Second Division for the club. In 1989 he signed for Football League newcomers Maidstone United. He was with the club for three years and played 76 times in the Football League Fourth Division, and was one of the club's final two registered players when they went bankrupt and resigned from the league in August 1992. He subsequently moved into non-league football with Kettering Town.

response: They were due to play their first game of the season away to Scunthorpe United on 15 August 1992 but by this stage only two players (defender Gary Stebbing and striker Glen Donegal) were still registered to the club, and the Watling Street stadium had been sold the previous month, leaving Maidstone without a home and not knowing where they would be playing their home games if they remained in existence.
